\c 27
\s1 The Altar [for Burnt Offering]
\p
\v 1 "Make an altar\f + fr 27:1 \fk altar \ft Altar was a [place to offer animal sacrifice to God//high table that often in the OT was made from rocks, that was used as a place to offer sacrifices to God]. This altar was made from wood so that it could be moved.\f* from acacia wood shaped square [long], with the length measurement of 2.2 meters, and width of 2.2 meters, and height of 1.3 meters.\f + \fr 27:1 \fk meter measurement \ft Literally, "five hastas long and five hastas wide, ... three hastas high."\f*
\v 2 Make four horns at the four corners [on top] of the altar in such a way that the horns are one with the altar. Then cover all of the altar with bronze.
\v 3 Make all of the altar's equipment from bronze— the place for ashes, shovels, basins, meat hooks, and charcoal holders.
\v 4 Make [roaster shaped like woven//baking order?] with latice\f + fr 27:4 \fk Latice \ft The latice that is meant here are holes like para-para? for roasting meat.\f* from bronze and connect four bronze [supporting] bracelets to its four corners.
\v 5 Attach the baking order with bronze latice beneath the edge of the altar. Be certain that this [roaster//baking order] is attached not more than half the height of the altar.
\v 6 Make carrying poles also for the altar from acacia wood and cover the poles with bronze.
\v 7 Attach those poles to the bracelets on the two sides of the altar.
\v 8 Make the altar like an empty box from cut boards, like what was shown to you on top of the mountain."
\s1 The Holy Tent's courtyard
\p
\s1 Pelataran
\p
\v 9 "Then make the courtyard for the Holy Tent, and fence it with curtains that are made from fine linen cloth. On the south side, that curtain has to be 44 meters long.
\v 10 Hang that curtain on twenty posts that are attached to twenty bronze bases using silver hooks and connectors.
\v 11 The same on the north side, make a curtain the same— with a length of 44 meter and hung from twenty posts with bronze bases [and] using silver hooks [and] silver connectors.
\v 12 On the west side, [the width] of the curtain [0//its width] of 22 meters, and hung from ten posts attached to ten bases.
\v 13 On the east side, where there is a gate door, the width of the courtyard has to be 22 meters.
\v 14-15 The curtain has to be hung on the left side and right of the gate door of the courtyard the curtain. The curtain on the right side has a length of 6.5 meters, hung on three posts that are placed on top of three bases. The curtain that is on the left side also has a length of 6.5 meters, hung on three posts that are placed on top of three bases.
\v 16 For the courtyard's gate door, make a curtain the length of 9 meters from fine linen cloth, and decorated with beautiful blue, purple and red colored embroidery. That curtain will hang from four posts that are placed on four bases.
\v 17 All of the posts around the courtyard each have to be connected with silver rods, using silver hooks. The posts' bases have to be made from bronze.
\v 18 So, the whole courtyard will measure 44 meters long and 22 meters wide, with the height of the curtains being 2.3 meters, being made from fine linen cloth and with posts made from bronze.
\v 19 All of the equipment of the Holy Tent and all of the bolts used to support the Holy Tent and the courtyard curtains must be made of bronze."
\s1 Oil for the lamps
\s1 Minyak
\p
\v 20 “Command the people of Israel to bring to you pure olive oil for the lamps, so that the lamps burn continuously.
\v 21 Aaron and his children are responsible to guard so that the lamps in the Holy Tent in front of the Most Holy Room curtain burn continuously before the LORD from evening to morning. This is a statute that lasts for the nation of Israel from generation to generation.